Celo’s governance covers both on-chain and off-chain changes. On-chain proposals modify the protocol’s smart contracts or parameters, such as:Upgrading core contracts (e.g., CELO or cUSD management).
Adding new stablecoins.
Adjusting validator election parameters or rewards.

Off-chain governance, categorized as General Governance, includes decisions that don’t directly alter the blockchain but impact the community, such as:Naming hard forks.
Community suggestions for ecosystem development.
Funding initiatives from the on-chain Community Fund, like regional support grants or educational programs.

